(146,'Tsuyoshi Shinozaki','+819077257519','goez.user3@gmail.com','Dear person in charge of imports\r\n \r\nHello.\r\nWe\'re GOEZ, the trading company in Japan, mainly dealing with sake and whisky. \r\n\r\nWe\'ve tried to have contact with you because Ms.Jennie (Sales Administration Manager at the Warehouse - Wine Merchants) who are wanting our products introduced you to us.\r\n \r\nThrough exports of sake and whisky, our company has proven results for five years, about 3 million dollars of exports per year, \r\nThen, we would make a proposal that your company would import Japanese premium sake and whisky, which some retail stores already want to buy, directly from our company.\r\n\r\nPlease let me know if you would like to see our list, including so many kinds of  Japanese premium sake like Juyondai, Dassai, Kubota and Aramasa, and Japanese premium whisky like Yamazaki, Hakushu, Hibiki and Taketsuru. \r\nThose products are so hard to get nowadays even in Japan, and we\'re sure that they will be so much more valuable in your country.\r\n\r\nBecause of such a crisis (COVID-19), we strongly think our business has to take on a new challenge. \r\nWe really hope you would be a good partner for this project.\r\n\r\nWe hope we could hear from you.\r\n \r\nBest regards,\r\n \r\nTsuyoshi Shinozaki \r\n \r\nGOEZ Co., Ltd. (http://goez.co.jp/ ) \r\n2-5-16 Shimomaruko \r\nOta-ku, Tokyo \r\nJapan \r\n',NULL,NULL,NULL),
(147,'Patrice','+79250052758','patrice@svamgroup.ru','Hello,\r\n\r\nLet me introduce myself, my name is Patrice Traore and I’m in charge of export at Gletcher Modern Russian Brewery.\r\n\r\nCurrently we are looking for a reliable importer and your company has been recommended as the one by Russian Foreign Trade Support mission.\r\n\r\nI would like to make a short introduction of our business in five facts about Brewery:\r\n\r\n•	Brewing tasty beers since 2011, located in a quiet Moscow satellite city Klin.\r\n•	Our portfolio consists of classic European styles such as lager, pils, hefeweizen, blanche, rouge, pale ale and IPA. As well as some seasonal and twisted craft beers.\r\n•	We use only imported raw materials, English and German barley and grains; American and European hops and a local water from artesian well filtered with reverse osmosis and mineralized.\r\n•	Brewery is equipped with machinery from world top suppliers, such as Krones and Paul Mueller. Some of our beers are marked with Vegan society sign.\r\n•	Among our partners are a variety of HoReCa outlets as well as grocery chains, such as Auchan, Metro C&C, Selgros C&C, Globus, Billa and others. We export to EU and CIS countries and are interested in development of export activities.\r\n\r\nI hope my short introduction caught your attention. Looking forward to hear from you soon, In case of any questions please don’t hesitate to contact me by e-mail, phone or WhatsApp.\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nPatrice',NULL,NULL,NULL),
